requests.documentation: Request from client to get the current snapshot of the type server. A snapshot is a point-in-time representation of the type server's state, including all loaded files and their types.
Request to get the version of the protocol the type server supports. Returns a string representation of the protocol version (should be semver format).
Request to get diagnostics for a specific file.
Request to get the version of diagnostics for a specific file.
Request to get the type information for a specific node.
Request to get the type information for a specific builtin type.
Request to get the collection of subtypes that make up a union type or the types that makes up a generic type.
Request to find symbols from a type.
Request to find symbols from a node.
Request to get all overloads of a function or method. The returned value doesn't include the implementation signature.
Request to get the overloads that a call node matches.
Request to get the meta class of a type.
Request to get the type of a declaration.
Request to get the string representation of a type in a human-readable format. This may or may not be the same as the type's "name".
Request to get the docstring for a specific declaration.
Request to resolve an import declaration.
Request to resolve an import. This is used to resolve the import name to its location in the file system.
Get information about a type alias.
Request to combine types. This is used to combine multiple types into a single type.
Request to generate an instance type representation for the provided type.
Request to get the search paths that the type server uses for Python modules.
Request to fetch category properties for the given type.

notifications.documentation: Notification sent by the server to indicate any outstanding snapshots are invalid.
Notification sent by the server to indicate that diagnostics have changed and the client should re-request diagnostics for the file.

structures.name: Position

properties.name: line
properties.documentation: Line position in a document (zero-based).

properties.name: character
properties.documentation: Character offset on a line in a document (zero-based).

structures.documentation: Position in a text document expressed as zero-based line and character offset.

structures.name: Range

properties.name: start
properties.documentation: The range's start position.

properties.name: end
properties.documentation: The range's end position.

structures.documentation: A range in a text document expressed as (zero-based) start and end positions.

structures.name: Diagnostic

properties.name: range
properties.documentation: The range at which the message applies.

properties.name: severity
properties.documentation: The diagnostic's severity.

properties.name: code
properties.documentation: The diagnostic's code.

properties.name: source
properties.documentation: A human-readable string describing the source of this diagnostic.

properties.name: message
properties.documentation: The diagnostic's message.

structures.documentation: Represents a diagnostic, such as a compiler error or warning.

structures.name: Node

properties.name: uri
properties.documentation: URI of the source file containing this node.

properties.name: range
properties.documentation: The range of the node in the source file. This is a zero-based range, meaning the start and end positions are both zero-based. The range uses character offsets the same way the LSP does.

structures.documentation: Represents a node in an AST (Abstract Syntax Tree) or similar structure.

structures.name: ModuleName

properties.name: leadingDots
properties.documentation: The leading dots in the module name. This is used to determine the relative import level.

properties.name: nameParts
properties.documentation: The parts of the module name, split by dots. For example, for `my_module.sub_module`, this would be `['my_module', 'sub_module']`.

structures.documentation: Represents a module name with optional leading dots for relative imports.

structures.name: Type

properties.name: handle
properties.documentation: Unique identifier for the type definition within the snapshot. A handle doesn't need to exist beyond the lifetime of the snapshot.

properties.name: category
properties.documentation: Essential classification of the Type.

properties.name: flags
properties.documentation: Flags describing the type.

properties.name: moduleName
properties.documentation: Name of the module the type comes from

properties.name: name
properties.documentation: Simple name of the type. For example, for a class `MyClass` in module `my_module`, this would be `MyClass`.

properties.name: aliasName
properties.documentation: The typing module defines aliases for builtin types (e.g. Tuple, List, Dict). This field holds the alias name.

properties.name: categoryFlags
properties.documentation: Flags specific to the category. For example, for a class type, this would be ClassFlags. For a function type, this would be FunctionFlags.

properties.name: categoryProperties
properties.documentation: Properties specific to the category, such as function parameters. Returned only if requested with `fetchPropertiesFlags`.

properties.name: decl
properties.documentation: Declaration of the type, if available.

structures.documentation: Represents a type in the type system.

structures.name: Properties

properties.name: fetchedPropertiesFlags
properties.documentation: Bit flags indicating which category-specific property blocks were fetched for this type.

structures.documentation: Base for category specific property containers. Includes bit flags indicating which properties are present.

structures.name: AnyProperties
structures.documentation: Currently empty extension of Properties reserved for future 'Any' category properties.

structures.name: FunctionProperties
structures.documentation: Currently empty extension of Properties reserved for future function-specific keys (e.g. parameter default summaries).

structures.name: OverloadedProperties
structures.documentation: Currently empty extension of Properties reserved for future overloaded-function specific keys.

structures.name: ClassProperties
structures.documentation: Currently empty extension of Properties reserved for future class-specific keys.

structures.name: ModuleProperties
structures.documentation: Currently empty extension of Properties reserved for future module-specific keys.

structures.name: UnionProperties
structures.documentation: Currently empty extension of Properties reserved for future union-specific keys.

structures.name: TypeVarProperties
structures.documentation: Currently empty extension of Properties reserved for future type variable-specific keys.

properties.name: handle
properties.documentation: Unique identifier for the declaration within the session.

properties.name: category
properties.documentation: Category of this symbol (function, variable, etc.).

properties.name: flags
properties.documentation: Extra information about the declaration.

properties.name: node
properties.documentation: Parse node associated with the declaration

properties.name: moduleName
properties.documentation: The dot-separated import name for the file that contains the declaration.

properties.name: name
properties.documentation: The symbol name for the declaration (as the user sees it)

properties.name: uri
properties.documentation: The file that contains the declaration. Unless this is an import declaration, then the uri refers to the file the import is referring to.

structures.documentation: Represents a symbol declaration in the type system.

structures.name: Symbol

properties.name: name
properties.documentation: The name of the symbol found.

properties.name: type
properties.documentation: The type of the symbol found.

properties.name: decls
properties.documentation: The declarations for the symbol. This can include multiple declarations for the same symbol, such as when a symbol is defined in multiple files.

properties.name: flags
properties.documentation: Flags giving more information about the symbol.

properties.name: parent
properties.documentation: The type that is the semantic parent of this symbol. For example if the symbol is for a parameter, the parent would be the function or method that contains the parameter. If the symbol is for a class member, the parent would be the class that contains the member.

structures.documentation: Symbol information for a node

enumerations.name: FetchPropertiesFlags

values.name: All
values.documentation: All fetchable properties. (0xFFFFFFFF)

enumerations.documentation: Flags controlling which category properties are fetched for a type.

enumerations.name: TypeCategory

values.name: Any
values.documentation: Type can be anything

values.name: Function
values.documentation: Callable type

values.name: Overloaded
values.documentation: Functions defined with @overload decorator

values.name: Class
values.documentation: Class definition

values.name: Module
values.documentation: Module instance

values.name: Union
values.documentation: Union of two or more other types

values.name: TypeVar
values.documentation: Type variable

enumerations.documentation: Represents a category of a type, such as class, function, variable, etc.

enumerations.name: TypeFlags

values.name: Instantiable
values.documentation: Indicates if the type can be instantiated.

values.name: Instance
values.documentation: Indicates if the type represents an instance (as opposed to a class or type itself).

values.name: Callable
values.documentation: Indicates if an instance of the type can be called like a function.

values.name: Literal
values.documentation: Indicates if the instance is a literal (like `42`, `"hello"`, etc.).

values.name: Interface
values.documentation: Indicates if the type is an interface (a type that defines a set of methods and properties).

values.name: Generic
values.documentation: Indicates if the type is a generic type (a type that can be parameterized with other types).

values.name: FromAlias
values.documentation: Indicates if the type came from an alias (a type that refers to another type).

values.name: Unpacked
values.documentation: Indicates if the type is unpacked (used with TypeVarTuple).

enumerations.documentation: Flags that describe the characteristics of a type. These flags can be combined using bitwise operations.

enumerations.name: FunctionFlags

values.name: Async
values.documentation: Indicates if the function is asynchronous.

values.name: Generator
values.documentation: Indicates if the function is a generator (can yield values).

values.name: Abstract
values.documentation: Indicates if the function is abstract (must be implemented in a subclass).

values.name: Static
values.documentation: Indicates if the function has a @staticmethod decorator.

values.name: GradualCallableForm
values.documentation: The *args and **kwargs parameters do not need to be present for this function to be compatible. This is used for Callable[..., x] and ... type arguments to ParamSpec and Concatenate.

enumerations.documentation: Flags that describe the characteristics of a function or method. These flags can be combined using bitwise operations.

enumerations.name: ClassFlags

values.name: Enum
values.documentation: Indicates if the class is an enum (a special kind of class that defines a set of named values).

values.name: TypedDict
values.documentation: Indicates if the class is a TypedDict or derived from a TypedDict.

enumerations.documentation: Flags that describe the characteristics of a class. These flags can be combined using bitwise operations.

enumerations.name: TypeVarFlags

values.name: IsParamSpec
values.documentation: Indicates if the type variable is a ParamSpec (as defined in PEP 612).

values.name: IsTypeVarTuple
values.documentation: Indicates if the type variable is a TypeVarTuple (as defined in PEP 646).

enumerations.documentation: Flags that describe the characteristics of a type variable. These flags can be combined using bitwise operations.

enumerations.name: DeclarationCategory

values.name: Intrinsic
values.documentation: An intrinsic refers to a symbol that has no actual declaration in the source code, such as built-in types or functions.

values.name: Variable
values.documentation: A variable is a named storage location that can hold a value.

values.name: Param
values.documentation: A parameter is a variable that is passed to a function or method.

values.name: TypeParam
values.documentation: This is for PEP 695 type parameters.

values.name: TypeAlias
values.documentation: This is for PEP 695 type aliases.

values.name: Function
values.documentation: A function is any construct that begins with the `def` keyword and has a body, which can be called with arguments.

values.name: Class
values.documentation: A class is any construct that begins with the `class` keyword and has a body, which can be instantiated.

values.name: Import
values.documentation: An import declaration, which is a reference to another module.

enumerations.documentation: Represents the category of a declaration in the type system.

enumerations.name: DeclarationFlags

values.name: ClassMember
values.documentation: Indicates if the declaration is a method (a function defined within a class).

values.name: Constant
values.documentation: Indicates if the declaration is a constant (a variable that cannot be changed).

values.name: Final
values.documentation: Indicates if the declaration is final variable (a class that cannot be subclassed).

values.name: IsDefinedBySlots
values.documentation: Indicates if the declaration is defined by slots (a class that uses __slots__).

values.name: UsesLocalName
values.documentation: Indicates if the import declaration uses 'as' with a different name.

values.name: UnresolvedImport
values.documentation: Indicates if the import declaration is unresolved (the module or symbol could not be found).

values.name: SimpleParam
values.documentation: Indicates if the declaration is a simple parameter (e.g., a function parameter).

values.name: ArgsListParam
values.documentation: Indicates if a declaration is an argument list (e.g., `*args`).

values.name: KwargsDictParam
values.documentation: Indicates if the declaration is a keyword argument dictionary (e.g., `**kwargs`).

values.name: PositionalParam
values.documentation: Indicates if the declaration is a positional parameter.

values.name: StandardParam
values.documentation: Indicates if the declaration is a standard parameter.

values.name: KeywordParam
values.documentation: Indicates if the declaration is a keyword parameter.

values.name: ExpandedArgsParam
values.documentation: Indicates if the declaration is an expanded *args parameter.

values.name: ReturnType
values.documentation: Indicates if the declaration is a return type (e.g., the return value of a function).

values.name: EnumMember
values.documentation: Indicates if the declaration is a member of an enum type.

values.name: TypeDeclared
values.documentation: Indicates if the declaration has an explicitly declared type.

values.name: SpecializedType
values.documentation: Indicates if the declaration is a specialization of a generic type.

enumerations.documentation: Flags that describe extra information about a declaration.

enumerations.name: SymbolSearchFlags

values.name: SkipInstanceAttributes
values.documentation: Skip instance attributes when searching for attributes of a type.

values.name: SkipTypeBaseClass
values.documentation: Skip members from the base class of a type when searching for members of a type.

values.name: SkipAttributeAccessOverrides
values.documentation: Skip attribute access overrides when searching for members of a type.

values.name: GetBoundAttributes
values.documentation: Look for bound attributes when searching for attributes of a type. That is methods bound specifically to an instance.

values.name: SkipUnreachableCode
values.documentation: When searching for a name, skip symbols that are in unreachable code.

enumerations.documentation: Flags that are used for searching for symbols.

enumerations.name: SymbolFlags

values.name: SynthesizedName
values.documentation: Indicates if the symbol name was synthesized by the type server and not present in the source code.

enumerations.documentation: Flags that give more information about a symbol.

enumerations.name: TypeReprFlags

values.name: ExpandTypeAliases
values.documentation: Turn type aliases into their original type.

values.name: PrintTypeVarVariance
values.documentation: Print the variance of a type parameter.

values.name: ConvertToInstanceType
values.documentation: Convert the type into an instance type before printing it.

values.name: PythonSyntax
values.documentation: Limit output to legal Python syntax.

enumerations.documentation: Flags that control how type representations are formatted.

typeAliases.name: FetchPropertyFlags
typeAliases.documentation: Alias for FetchPropertiesFlags provided for consumer convenience.

typeAliases.name: TypeHandle
typeAliases.documentation: Unique identifier for a type definition within the snapshot. A handle doesn't need to exist beyond the lifetime of the snapshot.

typeAliases.name: DeclarationHandle
typeAliases.documentation: Unique identifier for a declaration within the session.
